a,\ b,\ a\times b
1-(b\cdot b)=\lambda\alpha
\ \gamma(b\cdot a)=\lambda\beta
\ -\alpha=\lambda\gamma
x=\alpha a+\beta b+\gamma(a\times b)
a-\alpha(a\times b)+\gamma\cdot b\times (a\times b) = \lambda \alpha a+\lambda\beta b+ \lambda\gamma(a\times b) \\  a+\gamma\cdot((b\cdot a)b-(b\cdot b)a)-\alpha(a\times b)= \lambda \alpha a+\lambda\beta b+ \lambda\gamma(a\times b) \\ (1-(b\cdot b))a+(\gamma(b\cdot a))b-\alpha(a\times b)= \lambda \alpha a+\lambda\beta b+ \lambda\gamma(a\times b) 
\lambda\ne 0
\alpha=\frac{1-(b\cdot b)}{\lambda}
\ \gamma=-\frac{\alpha}{\lambda}\ 
\ \beta=\frac{\gamma(b\cdot a)}{\lambda}
\vec{a} + \vec{b} \times \vec{x} = \lambda\vec{x}
a_1\vec{i} + a_2\vec{j} + a_3\vec{k} + (b_2x_3-b_3x_2)\vec{i} - (b_1x_3-b_3x_1)\vec{j}+(b_1x_2-b_2x_1)\vec{k}=\lambda(x_1\vec{i}+x_2\vec{j}+x_3\vec{k})
